  "source": "Exact oracle values dumped from the REAL RMC.BestFit MaximumAPosteriori via tools/oracle_emitter --dump (M14) and reproduced by tools/verify_oracles.py. The same censored DataFrame construct as mle_censored.json (exact incl. flagged low outlier + low_outlier_threshold, interval, threshold, uncertain) fit by the posterior mode -- default flat parameter priors plus the Jeffreys 1/scale prior (UseJeffreysRuleForScale default), NelderMead. Point values rel 1e-9 (C++ reproduces the C# fit bit-for-bit). covariance/standard_error/correlation rel 5e-3, a DOCUMENTED looser tier than the Phase 4 1e-5 Hessian band: for O(1e4)-scale parameters NumericalDiff clamps the step to MaxStep = 1e-2, so the Hessian second difference (~H*h^2 ~ 1e-10) sits ~3e-4 above the |logL| ~ 144 double-rounding floor -- measured C++-vs-C# divergence is 2e-4..7e-4 (pure cancellation noise; the fit itself matches exactly). bic's arg is the sample size n=14 (the frame's total record length).",
